<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-28T12:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-28T12:24:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2852: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                </gloss>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-28T12:24:00-05:00">January
                                    28, 1952—12:24 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 852. Re Membership: Request
                            urgently answers to fol: <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Does your latest estimate indicate Sov <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Res has any chance receiving seven affirmative
                                    votes in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> or that Sov <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Res may obtain two-thirds vote in
                                    plenary?</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>When are <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> plenary expected take up
                                    membership?</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>